South Korea Stocks: Hyundai Merchant, Kepco Plant, Kia Motors

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-04-26T01:05:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/south-korea-stocks-hyundai-merchant-kepco-plant-kia-motors.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in South Korea trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:45 a.m. in Seoul. The  Kospi
Index (KOSPI)  fell 6.74, or 0.3 percent, to 2,209.26.  Hyundai Merchant Marine Co. (011200 KS) fell 4.4 percent to
32,450 won. The company posted an operating loss of 24.1 billion
won in the first quarter from a profit of 6.17 billion won a
year earlier, according to a filing.  Kepco Plant Service & Engineering Co. (051600 KS), which
provides maintenance services for  power plants , fell 3.2 percent
to 32,050 won. Korea Investment & Securities Co. cut its stock
rating to “hold” from “buy,” citing a “stalled” earnings
growth this year, in a report today.  Kia Motors Corp. (000270)  (000270 KS), an affiliate of Hyundai Motor
Co., added 3.7 percent to 83,500 won. The stock gained on
speculation first-quarter profit will top consensus estimates
and its U.S. market share will rise in the current quarter, Kim Doo Hyun, a Seoul-based analyst at Kiwoom Securities Co., said
by phone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
